race.comment: A good race. JOB DONE (1) made it two wins on the bounce at Caulfield Heath scoring by a head in a 74 over 1100m. Was backed off the map.and benefits from Bates' handy 2kg claim. Has a wide gate to contend with but with average luck will be hard to beat. FARAWAY DREAM (4) is also third-up seeking the hat-trick. She is free running and was heavily bet winning a 64 handsomely at Cranbourne last time. Carries 6.6kg less today and that brings her right into it. MISS OLE (2) resumes off wins this grade at Sandown-Hillside and Flemington. She's had two jumpouts and Ben Melham is reunited. It's his sole ride at the meeting and she won't have to improve much to go close. ESMAHLI (3) bounced straight back into the winners' circle delivering a 64 comfortably at Mornington. The outside barrier makes it tougher but he's sure to keep improving. ROYAL RENDEZVOUS (9) is in the mix building on his Maiden win at Werribee on debut.
